@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam stateBorderColor #333
skinparam stateBackgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam stateFontSize 12
skinparam arrowColor #666
skinparam defaultFontSize 10
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FEFCE8
skinparam noteBorderColor #CCC

title **FR-02: Registration Code — State Diagram**\n<size:10>Lifecycle states computed by registration_code_status()</size>

state "ACTIVE" as active #C8E6C9 {
  active : is_active = True
  active : archived_at = NULL
  active : times_used < max_uses
  active : expires_at > now
}

state "EXHAUSTED" as exhausted #FFE0B2 {
  exhausted : times_used >= max_uses
  exhausted : (is_active set to False
  exhausted :  during final redemption)
}

state "EXPIRED" as expired #FFCDD2 {
  expired : expires_at <= now
  expired : (time-based, automatic)
}

state "REVOKED" as revoked #E1BEE7 {
  revoked : is_active = False
  revoked : (manual deactivation
  revoked :  via PATCH endpoint)
}

state "ARCHIVED" as archived #CFD8DC {
  archived : archived_at = now()
  archived : (soft-delete, hidden
  archived :  from default list view)
}

[*] --> active : create_registration_codes()\nINSERT with is_active=True,\ntimes_used=0

active --> active : **Code redeemed**\n(times_used < max_uses - 1)\nredeem_student_invite()\nredeem_non_student_local_invite()\nredeem_non_student_oauth_invite()\nredeem_student_join_course()

active --> exhausted : **Final redemption**\ntimes_used reaches max_uses\nis_active set to False

active --> expired : **Time passes**\nexpires_at <= now\n(detected on next query)

active --> revoked : **Manual revoke**\ntransition_registration_code_status(\n  next_status="REVOKED")\nSets is_active = False

exhausted --> archived : **Archive**\ntransition_registration_code_status(\n  next_status="ARCHIVED")\nSets archived_at = now()

expired --> archived : **Archive**\ntransition_registration_code_status(\n  next_status="ARCHIVED")

revoked --> archived : **Archive**\ntransition_registration_code_status(\n  next_status="ARCHIVED")

note right of active
  **Status determination priority**
  (from registration_code_status):
  1. archived_at != NULL → ARCHIVED
  2. expires_at <= now → EXPIRED
  3. times_used >= max_uses → EXHAUSTED
  4. not is_active → REVOKED
  5. else → **ACTIVE**

  Priority means EXPIRED overrides
  EXHAUSTED and REVOKED when time
  passes (a revoked code becomes
  EXPIRED after its expiry date).
end note

note left of revoked
  **Revocation is permanent.**
  Cannot be un-revoked.
  Only transition out
  is to ARCHIVED.
end note

note bottom of archived
  **Archive = soft delete.**
  Hidden from GET /codes by default.
  Visible only with ?includeArchived=true.
  No further transitions possible.
end note

@enduml
